##My resume has nowhere to go

Micro Signal Xincaijing

Function introduction, the recorder of new business, the promoter of New Economy.

-- Yang Jie

Edited by gale

Chen Dongyuan, who has been floating in the workplace for five years, thought he could take it in stride if he resigned naked years ago.

In late December, Chen quit his job at a mid-sized Gaming Company. At 11 o'clock that evening, he called out to his friends, "what job opportunity you have, think of your brother. "

Due to the accumulation of too many negative emotions, Chen Dong is ready to have a good years to start again, the original psychological expectation is to rest for a month or two time. As the saying goes, "gold three silver four, " for the workplace old Chen Dong, take a few offers is not so difficult.

However, the "Black Swan" of the epidemic took off suddenly, many companies delayed the resumption of work, market conditions than Chen Dong wanted to be worse. From the beginning of the seventh day of the Lunar New Year, he began a four-part series: scanning job recruitment websites, looking for candidates, revising resumes, and so on. But he never found the right opportunity.

"People's mentality is too easy to collapse. " Looking for a job in the distant future, so that Chen could not help at the end of the phone broke a swear word.

Since the second week of the holiday, job searches have started to show a recovery, with job listings and job applications up 7 per cent and 6 per cent respectively from last year, according to Linkedin. In contrast, the recruitment market is slowly recovering, with job postings still down 20-35 per cent in spring 2020 compared with the same period last year.

Like Chen, job seekers are facing a change. Behind the change is the caution of the market, where everyone is thinking about how best to live.

As a result, job seekers in an epidemic face not only a disruption in their plans, but also problems such as a shortage of workers and increased competition.

Workers who are suddenly hit by the epidemic are faced with the problem of finding a job.

In the middle of an epidemic

"If I had a second chance, I probably wouldn't have done it naked, " Chen said, sending a face emoji to Zinccaijing.

Before the Spring Festival, Chen Dong is in the project group that faces structural adjustment. "The departments are going to merge. " All sorts of rumours began to circulate internally. Chen Dong suddenly some frustration, frustration is not their own to stay or go, but on hand responsible for the project feel sorry.

In the end, he resigned.

After leaving, Chen Dong also cast a few favorite companies, one after another to accept interview invitations, but years ago in a state of extreme relaxation.

But after that stage, the current anxiety about job hunting is real.

Since the beginning of the year, Chen has invested in 12 companies, accepted seven interview invitations, but has yet to receive any offers. "Some of the responses were less optimistic, and some of the positions were misaligned, " he concluded.

In his job search process, although companies are constantly updating recruitment needs, but more recruitment needs have been frozen. A few years ago, the promising job, has also been quietly shut down.

For Chen Dong who has saved some savings, money is not the first issue, the most important is the career planning.

After college and graduation has been in Hangzhou Chen Dong, accumulated contacts, resources more concentrated in Hangzhou. For now, he is keeping an eye out for jobs in Shanghai and Nanjing, but in other cities, for Chen, life and work are too much to restructure.

Job Seekers in the workplace map source network

Such agonies are not uncommon.

As part of the Internet wave, Guo checked out of her job at her former employer at the end of the year and began looking for a job after taking a break. In the first two months after her resignation, she almost always went out to meet friends and stayed up until four or five o'clock to read novels.

After a brief two-week Binge, it's mostly anxiety and confusion.

Guo Qiong began to invest in a few favorite companies, one after another to accept interview invitations, although there have been interviews, but Guo Qiong also faced an awkward situation: Big Companies Do not need people, small companies she does not look up to.

After the outbreak, the interview also began to change to online communication, if the talk is good, then arrange video interview. Over the past week, Guo Qiong almost every day holding a cell phone, and HR online communication.

"I opened my eyes in the morning and touched my phone. I opened my phone and started answering messages. " Guo Qiong, who has received an offer, is not so confused. She began to yearn for the busy work in the past, Miss the colleagues in the cubicle, even in the sleep disorder, began to reflect on the past year's work should be improved.

"All this time, work has given me the greatest sense of security, " Guo told Zncaijing.

The Spring Festival is supposed to be an active recruitment season, but the spring of 2020 is very difficult. Whether it is a new student or has resigned from the workplace, in addition to signs demand reduction, increased competition, job seekers are also facing traffic congestion, unable to arrive on time practical obstacles.

The original was expected to spring recruitment map source network

A shot rang out

In this special and difficult time, the suddenly hit workplace began a real worry, worried about the mortgage and car loans, as well as the alipay ant chant and the timely arrival of credit card bills.

In the face of great uncertainty, many people who are ready to jump ship and settle down.

"It's a good thing I didn't quit years ago. ". Wu Wen, who works for a shanghai-based company, said. She was glad she didn't quit a year ago, and in November her project team was reshuffled, and colleagues in her department started jumping ship one by one, or starting businesses.

"It was a really exciting time. " Wu began to envy his colleagues who had resigned. Seeing photos of former colleagues traveling among their circle of friends during the transition, Wu was even more impatient. "Back then, wechat groups were always talking to friends about leaving. "

The arrival of the epidemic ultimately shaped her decision. She began to be glad she had waited. If she had resigned, she would have had at least a long rest years later.

"Two of my friends were offered, but because of the epidemic, the company decided the labor cost was too high and canceled the offer, " Wu said.

The outbreak of the disease has led her to reorient herself, and to avoid the anxiety of being left out of the market, she has also started taking online courses to broaden her career options.

It's been two months since the outbreak. According to Linkedin, entry level jobs were the most affected during the outbreak, with job postings down 94% from the same period last year. This means that more competitive candidates stand out, such as whether they have core skills, clear career goals and plans.

Industry Reshuffle, company changes and office conditions and other factors, the most direct impact on job seekers.

Market conditions have changed, like dominoes, even if the epidemic has been gradually brought under control, but opportunities in the workplace, will not immediately return to the status quo ante.

The market shock, in addition to hard job-seekers, affected by the largest, and this year's graduates.

Wang Yuqi is a university in Zhejiang media major fresh graduates, if there is no epidemic, at this moment she is ready to spring recruitment. Now, students in Zhejiang Province are not allowed to go back to school for a short period of time, and some companies have started cloud interviews.

Among them, Ali, suning, tencent and other Internet companies have already gathered the offline spring fair online, including online platforms, seminars, video interviews and so on.

"there is no exact answer as to when, " Wang said, as she waited to be notified of the spring job fair and continued to send out resumes to other companies.

For her, checking job sites has become a way to ease her anxiety.

Even so, Wang Yuqi still felt resistance in the spring move. On the one hand, spring recruitment than the autumn competition, coupled with a small number of places, the application is easy to sink; on the other hand, because of the cancellation of the seminar, Video Interview Success Rate will also be affected.

At this particular moment, there aren't many options for recent graduates or those who are looking for a job after leaving their jobs.

Quandary

Under the epidemic, companies have been hit hard, and the number of jobs being filled has plummeted. In contrast, job seekers have begun intensive job hunting since February 3,

In the 10 days after the Spring Festival in 2020(2.3-2.12) , the demand for new jobs in the job market has halved from the same period in 2019, with small and micro enterprises with fewer than 100 employees having the biggest impact, according to data from BOSS Zhipin's "talent trends in the 10 days after the Spring Festival in 2020" , the demand for new talent dropped sharply by 61% .
Data from BOSS Zhipin Research Institute

In addition, as the market risk intensifies, job seekers for a strong sense of stability, job-hopping to consider the workplace began to delay job change. Small businesses face a simultaneous decline in demand and supply of talent.

Linkedin data also suggests that recent job seekers have been more cautious. The number of job applications from non-graduates on the linkedin platform has fallen since the Spring Festival, compared with the pre-spring festival period this year and the same period last year. With the exception of health care, the number of job postings is declining in all areas, and workers are becoming more cautious.

While job seekers are hard to find, companies are also hard to recruit.

The current epidemic affected a wide range of industries, many enterprises can not resume work on time, but some industries are rising against the trend. Huang Jing, who works for an online education company, had a batch of recruitment plans to push ahead years later, but the company accelerated in the rebound in traffic as its business was mainly online.

Since the seventh day of the first lunar month, she has been working online, screening candidates and arranging video interviews. In the past, there were at most a dozen preliminary interviews a day, but this season, as everything has shifted online, some candidates have resisted video interviews for one reason or another.

In spite of the grim job market, Huang has had fewer interviews than expected over the past few days, and there aren't many suitable resumes posted on job sites.

During the epidemic, because video interview, for the actual situation of the company is not a whole grasp, job seekers panic, the success rate has also been affected.

Drastic changes put companies and job seekers in a quandary.

Whose Dawn

This year's environment, indeed to job seekers shrouded in invisible pressure. "practice" or struggle, this is on the job seekers in front of the problem.

The current epidemic affected a wide range of industries, many enterprises can not resume work on time, and some even into operational difficulties, but overall, the trend will not change.

Whether it is macro or micro, the fluctuations of the enterprise occasionally occur, in this process, the enterprise to strong internal; and for individuals, calm mind is more important. Special period of job-hunting experience, but also from the side to the job-seekers more objective, clear basis for the judgment.

It's not all bad news on the job hunt.

On the one hand, for prepared job seekers, the real test of the time, they are also beginning to sum up and reflect on their core competitiveness in the end?

Career people fight for survival map source network

During the outbreak, Lu Jia quickly passed the "cloud interview" and opened a new career. From years ago, Lu Jia began to send a resume to the company, in years later, it is into the revised resume, send resume repeat status.

"I started sending out resumes on the second day of the Lunar New Year. " After returning to work, Lu Jia's submissions also received feedback. As of January 16, she had been offered offers from three companies.

On Balance, she chose one of them. "The employment contract is also the cloud sign up, the new person's training material is on-line. " In this way, Lu Jia went through the entire process on-line, the successful entry.

For those who are ready, a competitive job season is not as scary as it might seem; for those who aren't, anxiety and confusion can linger.

On the other hand, the demand for middle-and high-end talent, for jobs in hot fields, is increasing rather than decreasing.

According to recruitment data, the 2020 Spring Festival, in the high-end talent resume delivery peak later than in previous years. Within 5 working days after the Spring Festival, both the total amount of resume delivery and the peak value of resume delivery are about 80% of that before the spring festival. With the follow-up companies have entered the normal operation, resume delivery volume will continue to climb.

Demand is also picking up in some sectors. Among them, the Internet shows the advantage of light assets, and the demand for new high-end talents is the biggest.

Notably, the consumer goods industry also ranks in the top three, with 9.39 percent. After the outbreak, most people travel restrictions, dependence on consumer goods, especially daily necessities, and the rise of new retail and local life channels, driving the demand for talent.

Data from job hunting site

Individual job, have their own different experience, no one can represent the whole workplace, no matter what industry, need to inject fresh blood, people, is always the most important.

People in the workplace should keep their heads down and look up at the road. The workplace is a marathon, for everyone, this special period, more with their own race.

"opportunities are always reserved for those who are prepared, " Lu said. "The rules of the game are simple. ".
